    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "We report the near-complete genome sequence and phylogenetic analysis of a severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) Delta variant (B.1.617.2) strain. This variant is associated with increased transmission and immune evasion.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "Abstract"
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "and C1247F) (Fig. 1B) . L452R, T478K, and P681R are three key mutations in the spike protein; it has been suggested that they are responsible for making the strain more transmissible and infectious (8) .",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 198,
                    "end": 201,
                    "text": "(8)",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF7"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 12,
                    "end": 21,
                    "text": "(Fig. 1B)",
                    "ref_id": "FIGREF0"
                }
            ],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "It has been confirmed that this patient did not report any recent travel history or known contact with recent travelers, so it is possible that this infection resulted from local community transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 Delta variant (B.1.617.2) in Bangladesh in May 2021.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Data availability. The sequence has been deposited at GenBank under accession number MZ437368. The raw sequence reads have been deposited at the NCBI Sequence Read Archive (SRA) under BioProject accession number PRJNA741723 and SRA accession number SRP336330.",
            "cite_spans": [],
